f(x) = -3+2cos(x)
g(x) = cos(x-\dfrac{1}{4}\pi)-2 
s(x)=f(x)+g(x)
d(x)=f(x)-g(x)
s(x)=(-5+2\cos (x))+(\cos(x-\pi/4)-2)=2\cos(x)+\cos(x-\pi/4)-7,
d(x)=(-5+2\cos (x))-(\cos(x-\pi/4)-2)=2\cos(x)-\cos(x-\pi/4)-3.
